                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17130515" author="libenchao" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 11:03:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;`%` is introduced in SQL:2011, in calcite only `BABEL`/`LENIENT`/`MYSQL_5` conformance supports it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Flink, we have our own conformance, IMO, we can support it by changing `FlinkSqlConformance#isPercentRemainderAllowed`&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17130579" author="jark" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 11:58:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If % is included in SQL standard, I think it makes sense to allow it. Which setion mentions % operator in SQL:2011? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17130597" author="libenchao" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 12:16:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found it in wiki page&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. I haven&apos;t got one complete copy of SQL:2011 standard.&lt;br/&gt;
After simply changing it in `FlinkSqlConformance`, the calcite will throw other exceptions. Maybe it&apos;s not so easy to open it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modulo_operation&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modulo_operation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17130646" author="leonard xu" created="Wed, 10 Jun 2020 12:56:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jark&quot;&gt;jark&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=libenchao&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;libenchao&quot;&gt;libenchao&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percent sign has been supported in calcite&#160;1.14.0 (2017-10-01) &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; by our old friend &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sunjincheng121&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sunjincheng121&quot;&gt;sunjincheng121&lt;/a&gt;, I think we can support in Flink&#65292; maybe&#160;&#160;`FlinkSqlConformance` and&#160;`FlinkSqlOperatorTable` and some others need to adapt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-1897&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17133858" author="libenchao" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2020 02:59:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Leonard+Xu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Leonard Xu&quot;&gt;Leonard Xu&lt;/a&gt;&#160;I think you are right, we can support it this way. +1 to support it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17150247" author="fsk119" created="Thu, 2 Jul 2020 12:52:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jark&quot;&gt;jark&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;m very interested in this issue. Could you assign it to me? I&apos;m willing to solve it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17151459" author="libenchao" created="Sun, 5 Jul 2020 02:22:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed via 4b9f9fe35256462851dbb8e0076114c32e345243 (1.12.0)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
